  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nRight now, during and after the authorization code flow, only ID token is verified by default, because by default,  Quarkus OIDC uses ID token only for the security decisions and only propagates the access token to the downstream targets.\r\nThe code flow access token is always verified if users are requesting to check it for the roles, In all other cases, users can enforce it with the `quarkus.oidc.authentication.verify-access-token=true`.\r\n\r\nHowever, users should not be required to set `quarkus.oidc.authentication.verify-access-token=true` if the JWT access token is injected as  `JsonWebToken`. If the access token is visible to the user's code as `JsonWebToken` then it must be verified by default\r\n\r\nCC @calvernaz\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\nAnalyze the injection data, if `JsonWebToken` is injected, set  `quarkus.oidc.authentication.verify-access-token=true` in the OIDC Recorder",
